From: Trond Myklebust <trond.myklebust@primarydata.com>
Date: Wed, 12 Feb 2014 09:36:59 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] NFSv4.1: Fix wraparound issues in pnfs_seqid_is_newer()
Git-commit: 2c64c57dfc4b7946f7abd8af653f55af581bc2c3
Patch-mainline: v3.15
References: bnc#898675

Subtraction of signed integers does not have well defined wraparound
semantics in the C99 standard. In order to be wraparound-safe, we
have to use unsigned subtraction, and then cast the result.

Signed-off-by: Trond Myklebust <trond.myklebust@primarydata.com>
Acked-by: NeilBrown <neilb@suse.de>

---
 fs/nfs/pnfs.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- linux-3.12-SLE12.orig/fs/nfs/pnfs.c
+++ linux-3.12-SLE12/fs/nfs/pnfs.c
@@ -662,7 +662,7 @@ pnfs_destroy_all_layouts(struct nfs_clie
  */
 static bool pnfs_seqid_is_newer(u32 s1, u32 s2)
 {
-	return (s32)s1 - (s32)s2 > 0;
+	return (s32)(s1 - s2) > 0;
 }
 
 /* update lo->plh_stateid with new if is more recent */
